# DRAMAC CMS - Cursor AI Rules

## Memory Bank System (CRITICAL)

**MANDATORY RULE:** Update `/memory-bank/` files at the END of EVERY task.

See detailed instructions in `.cursor/rules/memory-bank.md`

### Quick Reference

**Before final commit on EVERY task:**
1. Update `/memory-bank/progress.md` - Add latest work section
2. Update `/memory-bank/activeContext.md` - Add to "Recent Work"
3. Commit memory bank: `git commit -m "docs: update memory bank with [date] [description]"`
4. Push: `git push origin main`

**NO TASK IS COMPLETE WITHOUT MEMORY BANK UPDATE.**

## Project Context

- **Project:** DRAMAC CMS - Enterprise modular CMS platform
- **Stack:** Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript, Supabase, PostgreSQL
- **Location:** Dashboard in `/next-platform-dashboard/`
- **Memory Bank:** `/memory-bank/` (read at start of every session)

## Key Patterns

- Always read memory bank files before starting work
- Document all architectural decisions
- Update memory bank after every task (mandatory)
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow existing patterns in systemPatterns.md
- Test changes before committing

## Memory Bank Files (Read at Session Start)

1. `/memory-bank/projectbrief.md` - Core requirements
2. `/memory-bank/productContext.md` - Product goals
3. `/memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` - Architecture patterns
4. `/memory-bank/techContext.md` - Tech stack
5. `/memory-bank/activeContext.md` - Current focus
6. `/memory-bank/progress.md` - Status tracking

**Full details:** See `.cursor/rules/memory-bank.md` and `.github/copilot-instructions.md`
